`isDisabled` to prevent the drop zone from accepting interactions. The zone is dimmed and the cursor indicates it is not interactive."},"271":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-14","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"Key"},"272":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-15","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"Description"},"273":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-16","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"`Tab`"},"274":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-17","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"Moves focus to the drop zone"},"275":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-18","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"`Enter` / `Space`"},"276":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-19","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#keyboard","content":"Opens the file picker so files can be selected without a pointer"},"277":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-20","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#screen-readers","content":"The drop zone renders a visually hidden `<button>` inside the container. Assistive technology discovers and announces this button as an interactive element — activating it opens the native file picker without a pointer."},"278":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-21","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#screen-readers","content":"The button's accessible name is built from two sources, combined in order:"},"279":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-22","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#screen-readers","content":"**`<Text slot=\"label\">`** — any `Text` child with `slot=\"label\"` has its `id` linked to the button via `aria-labelledby`. This is the recommended way to provide a contextual label that is also visible to sighted users."},"280":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-23","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#screen-readers","content":"**`aria-label`** — pass `aria-label` on the `DropZone` component to override or supplement the label (e.g. `aria-label=\"Upload profile photo\"`). When no `Text slot=\"label\"` is present and no `aria-label` is set, the button falls back to the default \"DropZone\" label provided by React Aria."},"281":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-24","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#best-practices","content":"Use the drop zone alongside a button-based file picker — drag-and-drop is a convenience, never the only way to upload."},"282":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-25","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#best-practices","content":"Replace the default text with `children` to communicate the accepted file types and size limits up front."},"283":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-26","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#best-practices","content":"Let the drop zone fill its container; constrain it with the surrounding layout rather than setting a fixed width on the component itself."},"284":{"id":"/docs/components/drop-zone-27","page_id":"/docs/components/drop-zone","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/drop-zone#best-practices","content":"Reflect upload state (validating, uploading, error) outside the drop zone so the target area stays clear and predictable."},"285":{"id":"/docs/components/field","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"page","content":"Field primitives","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field"},"286":{"id":"/docs/components/field-0","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"Composable primitives (Field, FieldLabel, FieldGroup, FieldError) for building form fields"},"287":{"id":"/docs/components/field-1","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#usage","content":"Usage"},"288":{"id":"/docs/components/field-2","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#fieldgroup-props","content":"FieldGroup props"},"289":{"id":"/docs/components/field-3","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#basic-example","content":"Basic example"},"290":{"id":"/docs/components/field-4","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"Composition"},"291":{"id":"/docs/components/field-5","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#positioning-controls-inside-the-group","content":"Positioning controls inside the group"},"292":{"id":"/docs/components/field-6","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"States"},"293":{"id":"/docs/components/field-7","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#examples","content":"Examples"},"294":{"id":"/docs/components/field-8","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#leading-control","content":"Leading control"},"295":{"id":"/docs/components/field-9","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#trailing-control","content":"Trailing control"},"296":{"id":"/docs/components/field-10","page_id":"/docs/components/field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/field#icon-accessories","content":"Icon accessories"},"297":{"id":"/docs/components/field-11","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**Composition primitives.** The field components (TextField, NumberField, DateField, Select, RadioGroup, CheckboxGroup) compose these internally — reach for those first. These primitives are also the building blocks for custom composite fields, e.g. an input and a select sharing one bordered box."},"298":{"id":"/docs/components/field-12","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"The field decoration is split into granular, composable pieces so the same structure is shared across every field:"},"299":{"id":"/docs/components/field-13","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`Field`** — stacks a field's label, control, description, and error in one consistently spaced column (pure layout — a `Flex` column with the standard field gap)."},"300":{"id":"/docs/components/field-14","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldLabel`** — names the field and flags whether it's required (wraps React Aria `Label`, rendering an optional `*` indicator)."},"301":{"id":"/docs/components/field-15","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldGroup`** — the bordered box that visually unites a field's controls and reflects their shared focus, disabled, and invalid state. Used only by \"boxed\" fields (TextField, NumberField, Select, DateField); presentationally it is a React Aria `Group`."},"302":{"id":"/docs/components/field-16","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldInput`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`FieldTextArea`** — the control the user types into (normalized React Aria `Input`/`TextArea` given antares spacing via `Box`)."},"303":{"id":"/docs/components/field-17","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldButton`** — an actionable control placed inside the box, such as the NumberField steppers or a search submit (a click target within the group)."},"304":{"id":"/docs/components/field-18","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldDescription`** — helper text that explains the field; renders nothing when empty (wraps the antares `Text` with `slot=\"description\"`)."},"305":{"id":"/docs/components/field-19","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"**`FieldError`** — surfaces the field's validation messages when it is invalid, and nothing when valid (a thin wrapper over React Aria `FieldError`)."},"306":{"id":"/docs/components/field-20","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field","content":"`FieldLabel`, `FieldDescription`, and `FieldError` each render `null` when they have no content, so callers pass `label` / `description` / `errorMessage` straight through without guarding."},"307":{"id":"/docs/components/field-21","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"A boxed field composes the primitives inside its React Aria field wrapper. Use\n`Field as={...}` to merge the field wrapper and the layout column into a single\nelement:"},"308":{"id":"/docs/components/field-22","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"A field without a box (RadioGroup / CheckboxGroup) composes `Field` + `FieldLabel` + `FieldError` and omits `FieldGroup`."},"309":{"id":"/docs/components/field-23","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#composition","content":"`FieldGroup` is purely presentational — it renders the styled `Group` and holds no React Aria context. The surrounding field wires value, disabled, and validation state into its controls."},"310":{"id":"/docs/components/field-24","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#positioning-controls-inside-the-group","content":"`FieldGroup` rounds its outer corners from DOM order: the group's CSS rounds the start corners of its **first child** and the end corners of its **last child**, so controls are seamless inside and rounded only at the box edges. Author children in visual order and the rounding follows — no per-control positioning prop. A lone control (a TextField input, a Select trigger) is both first and last, so it rounds both edges. The rules are RTL-safe (they use logical `start`/`end` corners)."},"311":{"id":"/docs/components/field-25","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"The states **disabled**, **readonly**, and **invalid** are applied by the field wrapper (e.g. TextField, NumberField, Select). The group reflects them via data attributes on the group."},"312":{"id":"/docs/components/field-26","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"State"},"313":{"id":"/docs/components/field-27","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"CSS Selector"},"314":{"id":"/docs/components/field-28","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"disabled — Applied when the field wrapper is disabled."},"315":{"id":"/docs/components/field-29","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-disabled]`"},"316":{"id":"/docs/components/field-30","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"invalid — Applied when the field wrapper is invalid (e.g. validation failed)."},"317":{"id":"/docs/components/field-31","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-invalid]`"},"318":{"id":"/docs/components/field-32","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"focus — Whether an element within the group has keyboard focus (for focus-ring styling)."},"319":{"id":"/docs/components/field-33","page_id":"/docs/components/field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field#states","content":"`[data-focused]`"},"320":{"id":"/docs/components/icon","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"page","content":"Icon","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon"},"321":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-0","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon","content":"Flexible SVG icon component with on-demand loading, automatic caching, and extensive customization options"},"322":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-1","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#features","content":"Features"},"323":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-2","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#installation","content":"Installation"},"324":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-3","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#props","content":"Props"},"325":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-4","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#prop-inheritance","content":"Prop Inheritance"},"326":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-5","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#basic-usage","content":"Basic Usage"},"327":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-6","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#size-variants","content":"Size Variants"},"328":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-7","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#customization","content":"Customization"},"329":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-8","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#slots","content":"Slots"},"330":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-9","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#component-hierarchy","content":"Component Hierarchy"},"331":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-10","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#available-slot-overrides","content":"Available Slot Overrides"},"332":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-11","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icons","content":"Custom Icons"},"333":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-12","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#adding-icons-synchronously","content":"Adding Icons Synchronously"},"334":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-13","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#adding-icons-asynchronously","content":"Adding Icons Asynchronously"},"335":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-14","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#custom-icon-apis","content":"Custom Icon APIs"},"336":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-15","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#notes","content":"Notes"},"337":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-16","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#styling","content":"Styling"},"338":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-17","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#css-classes","content":"CSS Classes"},"339":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-18","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#data-attributes","content":"Data Attributes"},"340":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-19","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#color-customization","content":"Color Customization"},"341":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-20","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#inherit-from-parent-default","content":"Inherit from Parent (Default)"},"342":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-21","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#explicit-colors","content":"Explicit Colors"},"343":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-22","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#icon-transformations","content":"Icon Transformations"},"344":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-23","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#rotation","content":"Rotation"},"345":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-24","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#flipping","content":"Flipping"},"346":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-25","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#loading-states","content":"Loading States"},"347":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-26","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#placeholder-content","content":"Placeholder Content"},"348":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-27","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#accessibility","content":"Accessibility"},"349":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-28","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#decorative-icons","content":"Decorative Icons"},"350":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-29","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#semantic-icons","content":"Semantic Icons"},"351":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-30","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#interactive-icons","content":"Interactive Icons"},"352":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-31","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-considerations","content":"Performance Considerations"},"353":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-32","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#default-icon-loading","content":"Default Icon Loading"},"354":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-33","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#sprite-mode-optimization","content":"Sprite Mode Optimization"},"355":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-34","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#recommendations","content":"Recommendations"},"356":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-35","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#troubleshooting","content":"Troubleshooting"},"357":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-36","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#icon-not-loading","content":"Icon Not Loading"},"358":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-37","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/icon#performance-issues","content":"Performance Issues"},"359":{"id":"/docs/components/icon-38","page_id":"/docs/components/icon","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/icon","content":"The `Icon` component provides a flexible and performant way to display SVG icons with extensive customization options. Built on top of the Bento Icon system, it features on-demand loading from a CDN, automatic ca